c: 7
v: 169
t: "Then they were succeeded by an evil generation who inherited the Book; they indulged in the vanities of this nether life, saying: \"We expect to be forgiven\" assuming that they are favorites of Allah and somehow He will spare them. Yet if similar vanities come their way they would again seize them. Was not a covenant taken from them in the Book that they would not speak anything about Allah except the truth? And they have studied what is in the Book. Best for the righteous is the home of the hereafter, don’t you understand"